modules.description: Performs numerical integration of initial value problems using adaptive step size control, with functions to advance a single step or solve over a time interval. Operates on matrix-based state representations and functions that map states and time to updated states. Used for simulating dynamic systems where the state evolves according to a defined differential equation.

Provides root-finding, adaptive time-stepping, and implicit integration for systems of ordinary differential equations. Operates on real-valued vectors and matrices with automatic detection of state size. Enables simulation of dynamic systems such as chemical reaction networks and mechanical models.

Integrates initial value problems using adaptive step control, handling matrix-based states and time-dependent update functions to model dynamic systems. Supports both single-step advancement and interval-based solutions, enabling precise simulation of evolving states. Key operations include stepping through time and solving over ranges, with state transitions defined by user-provided functions. Examples include modeling physical systems, population dynamics, and chemical reactions.
